### INTENT ###
Add deterministic compatibility and conflict checks to the governed rule-registry validator. Keep this slice separate from completeness checks, coverage expansion, release work, GUI work, and documentation migration.

### NEW VALIDATOR RULES ###
- category/enforcement_phase combinations must match the explicit compatibility matrix.
- active mechanisms must not share the same category, priority, and enforcement_phase because that creates ambiguous enforcement order.
- same category and phase is allowed when priority differs.

### TEST COVERAGE ###
- current repository state validates.
- CLI still passes current repository state.
- incompatible category/phase is rejected.
- ambiguous category+priority+phase is rejected.
- same category/phase with different priority is accepted.
- previous classification, migration, and source-term tests remain active.

### OUT OF SCOPE ###
